18#include "AZToken.h"
19#include <vector>
20
21namespace ZXing {
22namespace Aztec {
23
24class Token;
25
26/**
27* State represents all information about a sequence necessary to generate the current output.
28* Note that a state is immutable.
29*/
30class EncodingState
31{
32public:
33 // The list of tokens that we output. If we are in Binary Shift mode, this
34 // token list does *not* yet included the token for those bytes
35 std::vector<Token> tokens;
36
37 // The current mode of the encoding (or the mode to which we'll return if
38 // we're in Binary Shift mode.
39 int mode;
40
41 // If non-zero, the number of most recent bytes that should be output
42 // in Binary Shift mode.
43 int binaryShiftByteCount;
44
45 // The total number of bits generated (including Binary Shift).
46 int bitCount;
47};
48
49} // Aztec
50} // ZXing
